description: Number of covers of an unlabeled n-set.
references: F. Bergeron, G. Labelle and P. Leroux, Combinatorial Species and Tree-Like Structures, Cambridge, 1998, pg 78 (2.3.39)
example: There are 4 nonisomorphic covers of {1,2}, namely {{1},{2}}, {{1,2}}, {{1},{1,2}} and {{1},{2},{1,2}}.
crossrefs: Cf. A003465 (labeled case). Differences of A000612.
author: _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jun 04 2000
extensions: More terms from David Moews (dmoews(AT)xraysgi.ims.uconn.edu) Jul 04 2002
